27
00:02:18,988 --> 00:02:21,571
[Episode 10]

28
00:02:34,337 --> 00:02:40,197
[Saetbyeol Daycare Annual Recital]

29
00:02:42,445 --> 00:02:43,972
Oh well,

30
00:02:43,972 --> 00:02:46,148
at least somebody came.

31
00:02:53,581 --> 00:02:57,418
What a poised performance
from our Giraffe class!

32
00:02:57,418 --> 00:02:58,461
Up next,

33
00:02:58,461 --> 00:03:00,713
the cutest little ones,

34
00:03:00,713 --> 00:03:02,506
our Deer class, are taking the stage!

35
00:03:02,506 --> 00:03:05,434
Give them a warm welcome!

36
00:03:14,877 --> 00:03:16,963
Woo Joo's got this, right?

37
00:03:16,963 --> 00:03:19,315
Of course, look whose nephew he is.

38
00:03:19,315 --> 00:03:20,942
Look, Woo Joo's the only kid up there

39
00:03:20,942 --> 00:03:23,243
without a worry in the world.

40
00:03:42,363 --> 00:03:43,614
Here comes Woo Joo!

41
00:03:43,614 --> 00:03:45,575
Woo Joo!

42
00:03:47,218 --> 00:03:49,428
You killed it today.

43
00:03:49,428 --> 00:03:52,774
You're a total natural on stage.

44
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:53,791
Woo Joo!

45
00:03:53,791 --> 00:03:55,710
This is for you!

46
00:03:56,961 --> 00:03:58,437
I'll snap one of you two.

47
00:03:58,437 --> 00:03:59,547
Sure.

48
00:03:59,547 --> 00:04:01,274
Woo Joo, look over there!

49
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:02,191
Okay, say cheese!

50
00:04:02,191 --> 00:04:04,068
- One, two, three!
- Peace!

51
00:04:04,068 --> 00:04:05,136
Peace!

52
00:04:05,136 --> 00:04:06,429
One, two, three!

53
00:04:06,429 --> 00:04:08,681
Peace.

54
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:11,450
I love Auntie.

55
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:13,668
What was that?

56
00:04:14,770 --> 00:04:17,190
I love Auntie.

57
00:04:18,107 --> 00:04:20,526
You love Auntie that much?

58
00:04:20,526 --> 00:04:23,238
I love Auntie.

59
00:04:24,155 --> 00:04:25,423
[Saetbyeol Daycare]

60
00:04:25,423 --> 00:04:26,882
Hyun Jin.

61
00:04:26,882 --> 00:04:27,633
Yes?

62
00:04:27,633 --> 00:04:28,718
Can I get a shot for you?

63
00:04:28,718 --> 00:04:31,012
No, we're all good. We already got some.

64
00:04:31,012 --> 00:04:33,556
Nice to meet you. You're so handsome.

65
00:04:33,556 --> 00:04:36,417
I'm Ga Eul's mom. She's Woo Joo's friend.

66
00:04:36,417 --> 00:04:39,186
You should get one of all three!
Don't you think?

67
00:04:39,186 --> 00:04:41,689
Would you mind getting one of us?

68
00:04:41,689 --> 00:04:42,898
Oh, absolutely!

69
00:04:42,898 --> 00:04:44,775
I'll take as many as you want!

70
00:04:44,775 --> 00:04:46,861
Woo Joo, picture time?

71
00:04:46,861 --> 00:04:48,870
Picture.

72
00:04:49,530 --> 00:04:52,116
Okay, smile!

73
00:04:52,116 --> 00:04:54,417
Oh, Woo Joo, you're so cute!

74
00:04:55,686 --> 00:04:57,480
So cute.

75
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:18,351
What's all that?

76
00:05:18,351 --> 00:05:21,479
Hang on, why are you here?

77
00:05:21,479 --> 00:05:24,431
Didn't you have your nephew's show?

78
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:28,361
It seemed fine without me there.

79
00:05:28,361 --> 00:05:29,570
What about you, though?

80
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:31,238
Why did you come back?

81
00:05:31,238 --> 00:05:33,206
And what's with the box?

82
00:05:35,826 --> 00:05:37,703
Isn't it obvious?

83
00:05:37,703 --> 00:05:39,455
I came to clear out my things.

84
00:05:39,455 --> 00:05:43,341
You're actually leaving for good?

85
00:05:44,001 --> 00:05:46,303
I made it official today.

86
00:05:47,588 --> 00:05:49,924
I knew this was coming,

87
00:05:49,924 --> 00:05:52,225
but now that the divorce is real,

88
00:05:54,637 --> 00:05:56,479
it just feels...

89
00:05:58,682 --> 00:06:00,498
so weird.

90
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:03,062
Wait.

91
00:06:03,062 --> 00:06:05,780
Are those tears?

92
00:06:08,734 --> 00:06:12,370
Then you shouldn't have signed.

93
00:06:14,056 --> 00:06:16,537
Don't cry. It's okay.

94
00:06:17,977 --> 00:06:19,979
Please don't cry.

95
00:06:22,957 --> 00:06:24,991
Good boy, eat up.

96
00:06:25,835 --> 00:06:26,836
Check this out!

97
00:06:26,836 --> 00:06:28,086
So adorable, right?

98
00:06:29,547 --> 00:06:31,507
Woo Joo, look, that's you!

99
00:06:31,507 --> 00:06:33,092
So cute.

100
00:06:33,092 --> 00:06:34,927
Seriously, he looks great.

101
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:38,305
You're the only reason
I even have a video of this.

102
00:06:38,305 --> 00:06:41,058
I couldn't take my eyes off Woo Joo.

103
00:06:41,058 --> 00:06:42,184
By the way,

104
00:06:42,184 --> 00:06:44,270
how did you find out about this?

105
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,813
Se Yeon mentioned it.

106
00:06:45,813 --> 00:06:48,983
I once went to my cousin's recital

107
00:06:48,983 --> 00:06:52,319
and was surprised by how many relatives
turned out for it.

108
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:54,822
So I figured I'd swing by.

109
00:06:54,822 --> 00:06:56,866
Besides, a good-looking uncle

110
00:06:56,866 --> 00:06:58,951
boosts Woo Joo's street cred.

111
00:06:58,951 --> 00:06:59,954
Right?

112
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:05,332
I really appreciate it.

113
00:07:05,332 --> 00:07:08,009
You're always helping me out.

114
00:07:09,712 --> 00:07:11,922
You know, hearing that

115
00:07:11,922 --> 00:07:14,508
actually stings a little.

116
00:07:14,508 --> 00:07:16,552
What?

117
00:07:16,552 --> 00:07:18,053
I don't know,

118
00:07:18,053 --> 00:07:20,723
it just feels like you're keeping distance.

119
00:07:20,723 --> 00:07:22,475
Between us, a little help like this

120
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:24,768
is no big deal. Just let me help.

121
00:07:24,768 --> 00:07:26,528
It's okay.

122
00:08:27,982 --> 00:08:31,110
He's really taking all of that?

123
00:08:34,947 --> 00:08:38,159
That looks like a full move-out.

124
00:08:41,787 --> 00:08:42,930
Well, yeah.

125
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:45,307
With all the years I gave this place,

126
00:08:45,307 --> 00:08:47,342
this is the bare minimum.

127
00:08:53,382 --> 00:08:55,150
For real, though,

128
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:57,352
you're set on leaving?

129
00:08:59,337 --> 00:09:01,982
I already told you, it's done.

130
00:09:02,658 --> 00:09:03,993
Plus,

131
00:09:03,993 --> 00:09:06,245
I've got a plane ticket.

132
00:09:06,245 --> 00:09:07,621
Staying here in Korea,

133
00:09:07,621 --> 00:09:09,906
I'll keep thinking about her.

134
00:09:10,749 --> 00:09:14,461
Will you really be all right?

135
00:09:14,461 --> 00:09:15,713
I know

136
00:09:15,713 --> 00:09:18,181
you still have feelings for her.

137
00:09:19,466 --> 00:09:22,477
How can you walk away like this?

138
00:09:24,167 --> 00:09:26,181
Can you tell?

139
00:09:26,181 --> 00:09:29,150
Oh, big time.

140
00:09:30,436 --> 00:09:32,237
It doesn't matter anyway.

141
00:09:33,731 --> 00:09:34,898
She clearly doesn't need me

142
00:09:34,898 --> 00:09:37,283
in her life anymore.

143
00:09:38,652 --> 00:09:40,487
That's how it's always been.

144
00:09:40,487 --> 00:09:43,866
My feelings were always deeper,

145
00:09:43,866 --> 00:09:46,327
and I was always running after her.

146
00:09:46,327 --> 00:09:47,828
You've seen it yourself.

147
00:09:47,828 --> 00:09:49,022
All those flashy people

148
00:09:49,022 --> 00:09:52,073
constantly around her.

149
00:09:53,323 --> 00:09:56,529
I doubt she ever felt the same.

150
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:58,672
Nobody stays with someone 20 years

151
00:09:58,672 --> 00:10:01,057
without caring at all.

152
00:10:04,178 --> 00:10:05,638
Maybe you're right.

153
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:07,431
Listen, Tae Hyung,

154
00:10:07,431 --> 00:10:08,766
when I'm gone,

155
00:10:08,766 --> 00:10:11,185
keep Filmpluto in good hands.

156
00:10:11,185 --> 00:10:13,646
I poured my best years into it,

157
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:16,131
so don't let it go downhill.

158
00:10:16,131 --> 00:10:18,025
When's your flight?

159
00:10:18,025 --> 00:10:20,052
The 13th, evening.

160
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:23,364
What, planning to see me off?

161
00:10:23,364 --> 00:10:25,157
Maybe, if I'm free.

162
00:10:25,157 --> 00:10:27,284
You're

163
00:10:27,284 --> 00:10:29,736
surprisingly loyal.

164
00:10:31,246 --> 00:10:32,623
Thanks.

165
00:10:32,623 --> 00:10:34,358
I jotted down some stuff

166
00:10:34,358 --> 00:10:36,418
that still needs covering,

167
00:10:36,418 --> 00:10:37,586
and put it all in a document.

168
00:10:37,586 --> 00:10:39,713
It's sitting on the table,

169
00:10:39,713 --> 00:10:41,821
so check it out when you're free.

170
00:11:09,292 --> 00:11:10,911
What are you doing here?

171
00:11:10,911 --> 00:11:12,795
I need to tell you something.

172
00:11:13,747 --> 00:11:15,582
Word got to me already.

173
00:11:15,582 --> 00:11:17,742
The divorce is finalized.

174
00:11:19,461 --> 00:11:21,221
Honestly, though,

175
00:11:21,839 --> 00:11:24,124
it's like none of this fazes you.

176
00:11:24,883 --> 00:11:26,927
This was inevitable.

177
00:11:26,927 --> 00:11:29,462
We haven't lived together in ages.

178
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:34,050
I wish I could shrug it off like you.

179
00:11:35,711 --> 00:11:37,922
The moment my stamp hit that paper,

180
00:11:38,772 --> 00:11:40,932
reality just sank in.

181
00:11:43,633 --> 00:11:45,780
This chapter is closed for good.

182
00:11:48,741 --> 00:11:50,576
Starting now,

183
00:11:50,576 --> 00:11:52,986
I'm done with Filmpluto.

184
00:11:54,121 --> 00:11:56,297
I at least owed you

185
00:11:57,249 --> 00:11:59,659
a proper farewell in person.

186
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:05,174
Are you sure

187
00:12:06,091 --> 00:12:08,334
you'll be fine on your own?

188
00:12:12,139 --> 00:12:14,357
I'll manage just fine.

189
00:12:15,517 --> 00:12:16,877
Well,

190
00:12:16,877 --> 00:12:18,796
two decades together means

191
00:12:18,796 --> 00:12:22,007
there's nothing left unseen,

192
00:12:22,007 --> 00:12:23,593
is there?

193
00:12:26,929 --> 00:12:28,989
Right.

194
00:12:28,989 --> 00:12:31,483
We both put in more than enough.

195
00:12:52,194 --> 00:12:53,896
Take care.

196
00:13:11,782 --> 00:13:13,992
What am I eating tonight?

197
00:13:13,992 --> 00:13:16,194
My back.

198
00:13:17,704 --> 00:13:20,258
Gosh.

199
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:22,751
I told you to see a doctor sooner.

200
00:13:22,751 --> 00:13:25,703
It wasn't even bothering me today...

201
00:13:26,922 --> 00:13:29,833
My nap probably did this to me.

202
00:13:32,678 --> 00:13:33,846
This is no good.

203
00:13:33,846 --> 00:13:34,763
Put some clothes on.

204
00:13:34,763 --> 00:13:36,932
That place by the intersection is still open.

205
00:13:36,932 --> 00:13:37,750
Get changed, now.

206
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,685
What? Why would I go there...

207
00:13:39,685 --> 00:13:42,254
Seriously, Mom!

208
00:13:42,254 --> 00:13:43,981
You know what drives me crazy?

209
00:13:43,981 --> 00:13:46,224
Ignoring a problem till it's bad!

210
00:13:47,943 --> 00:13:49,570
All right, I get it.

211
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:50,988
I'll go.

212
00:13:50,988 --> 00:13:54,199
I'll go to the doctor, okay?

213
00:13:54,199 --> 00:13:57,412
But it's almost time to pick up Woo Joo.

214
00:13:57,412 --> 00:13:59,204
Leave that to me, I'll call.

215
00:13:59,204 --> 00:14:01,865
Just change so we can head out.

216
00:14:12,868 --> 00:14:14,328
[Woo Hyun Jin]

217
00:14:14,328 --> 00:14:17,890
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

218
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:19,079
Goodbye!

219
00:14:19,079 --> 00:14:20,726
Bye, Woo Joo.

220
00:14:20,726 --> 00:14:22,519
Bye-bye.

221
00:14:22,519 --> 00:14:24,831
Woo Joo, did you miss me?

222
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:29,610
I missed you so much.

223
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:31,454
I think you grew since I last saw you.

224
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:33,188
You got heavier.

225
00:14:33,822 --> 00:14:35,516
Woo Joo,

226
00:14:35,516 --> 00:14:37,734
how about a day out, just us?

227
00:14:38,697 --> 00:14:41,021
I want to hang out, just us two.

228
00:14:41,021 --> 00:14:43,274
Let's go.

229
00:14:47,063 --> 00:14:49,880
I did some research,

230
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:53,166
and it says reading to babies early on
makes them smarter.

231
00:14:54,801 --> 00:14:57,012
Check this out.

232
00:14:57,012 --> 00:14:58,472
All right.

233
00:14:58,472 --> 00:15:00,131
Woo Joo.

234
00:15:01,224 --> 00:15:03,343
What's your pick out of these two?

235
00:15:08,482 --> 00:15:09,650
The toy wins, huh?

236
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:10,567
- Yeah.
- Oh really?

237
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:12,886
Books are still important, though.

238
00:15:12,886 --> 00:15:13,904
Get over here.

239
00:15:13,904 --> 00:15:14,821
Leave that there

240
00:15:14,821 --> 00:15:16,740
and we'll pick up some books.

241
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:17,991
Look at you being so obedient.

242
00:15:17,991 --> 00:15:19,882
Come here.

243
00:15:21,828 --> 00:15:22,871
Woo Joo.

244
00:15:22,871 --> 00:15:24,247
Welcome to my home.

245
00:15:24,247 --> 00:15:25,791
Pretty cool, right?

246
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:27,742
Jump!

247
00:15:30,897 --> 00:15:33,006
That's dangerous!

248
00:15:33,006 --> 00:15:33,757
It's pretty, right?

249
00:15:33,757 --> 00:15:35,425
If this drops, it's an ouchie,

250
00:15:35,425 --> 00:15:36,635
so we only use our eyes, okay?

251
00:15:36,635 --> 00:15:37,636
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

252
00:15:37,636 --> 00:15:39,545
So pretty.

253
00:15:41,807 --> 00:15:43,809
Woo Joo, you curious?

254
00:15:43,809 --> 00:15:45,431
Huh?

255
00:15:51,817 --> 00:15:53,177
- Woo Joo.
- Yeah.

256
00:15:53,177 --> 00:15:57,390
Careful. If that drops, it'll hurt,
and I'll have to blow on it.

257
00:15:57,390 --> 00:15:58,466
Right?

258
00:16:03,328 --> 00:16:05,530
Watch out, Woo Joo.

259
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,219
I wonder if these floors are too stiff for him.

260
00:16:14,198 --> 00:16:17,534
What's with that look? Come here.

261
00:16:17,534 --> 00:16:19,511
Hey, Sun Woo Joo.

262
00:16:19,511 --> 00:16:21,538
Seems like my home is a hit?

263
00:16:21,538 --> 00:16:23,416
Even filled a diaper already, huh?

264
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,727
Over here, time for a fresh diaper.

265
00:16:26,727 --> 00:16:29,271
Oh boy.

266
00:16:29,271 --> 00:16:31,222
You really went for it.

267
00:16:45,329 --> 00:16:47,149
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

268
00:16:48,123 --> 00:16:50,067
Oh...

269
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:51,534
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

270
00:16:53,587 --> 00:16:55,672
This one's called Ruri.

271
00:16:55,672 --> 00:16:56,631
And her name is?

272
00:16:56,631 --> 00:16:57,591
Her name, Ruri.

273
00:16:57,591 --> 00:16:58,800
Ruri.

274
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,261
Little Ruri was an adorable baby dino

275
00:17:01,261 --> 00:17:03,972
with a sweet tooth.

276
00:17:03,972 --> 00:17:05,015
You're adorable too, right?

277
00:17:05,015 --> 00:17:06,641
- Yeah.
- Right?

278
00:17:06,641 --> 00:17:07,851
Mama Dino grinned and said,

279
00:17:07,851 --> 00:17:11,354
"I whipped up something healthy

280
00:17:11,354 --> 00:17:13,739
just for you today."

281
00:17:15,025 --> 00:17:17,611
When you huff and puff,

282
00:17:17,611 --> 00:17:19,571
a hole opens up

283
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:20,781
in the great big...

284
00:17:20,781 --> 00:17:22,407
Cotton candy.

285
00:17:22,407 --> 00:17:23,621
Right.

286
00:17:23,621 --> 00:17:26,480
[Temporary housing]

287
00:17:45,122 --> 00:17:47,250
Look at you ringing the bell.

288
00:17:59,303 --> 00:18:01,321
I bought Woo Joo some books

289
00:18:01,321 --> 00:18:03,490
and he loved them.

290
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,075
Thanks.

291
00:18:05,075 --> 00:18:06,910
Things were so crazy for me today

292
00:18:06,910 --> 00:18:09,404
that Doo Sik's text totally slipped my mind.

293
00:18:10,205 --> 00:18:12,924
At least I got it, so it's all good.

294
00:18:16,378 --> 00:18:18,121
I should head out.

295
00:18:21,341 --> 00:18:23,618
Oh, right.

296
00:18:23,618 --> 00:18:25,846
With her back problems,

297
00:18:25,846 --> 00:18:28,932
the daycare runs for Woo Joo
aren't possible for a while.

298
00:18:28,932 --> 00:18:31,601
Yeah, I heard.

299
00:18:31,601 --> 00:18:33,979
I can grab him after daycare.

300
00:18:33,979 --> 00:18:37,649
Any day I'm not on set works.

301
00:18:37,649 --> 00:18:41,644
I'd owe you big time for that.

302
00:18:42,237 --> 00:18:44,322
She said keeping Woo Joo

303
00:18:44,322 --> 00:18:46,199
at her house is still fine,

304
00:18:46,199 --> 00:18:47,450
so after you get him,

305
00:18:47,450 --> 00:18:50,328
just bring him over to hers.

306
00:18:50,328 --> 00:18:52,129
Go on inside.

307
00:18:53,498 --> 00:18:56,242
Woo Joo, I'm off now.

308
00:19:00,338 --> 00:19:02,373
Bye-bye.

309
00:19:09,628 --> 00:19:11,766
Are you enjoying your book?

310
00:19:11,766 --> 00:19:13,442
Yeah?

311
00:19:14,294 --> 00:19:15,810
Look at you, reading all by yourself.

312
00:19:15,810 --> 00:19:19,807
Keep reading,
I'll be right back after I clean this up.

313
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:51,306
What's this?

314
00:19:51,306 --> 00:19:53,816
How did he forget to take this?

315
00:20:10,450 --> 00:20:13,620
Is he even eating properly?

316
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:16,197
He's skin and bones.

317
00:20:52,248 --> 00:20:54,690
Time to put your clothes on.

318
00:20:55,607 --> 00:20:57,823
All right.

319
00:21:00,396 --> 00:21:02,535
How handsome!

320
00:21:12,065 --> 00:21:14,035
Forget it, I'll finish this after I get back.

321
00:21:14,035 --> 00:21:15,578
Woo Joo, let's go.

322
00:21:15,578 --> 00:21:17,337
Give me your hand.

323
00:21:22,854 --> 00:21:24,079
Let's go.

324
00:21:24,079 --> 00:21:26,593
Let's go.

325
00:21:26,593 --> 00:21:28,562
Let's go.

326
00:21:33,892 --> 00:21:35,603
Get in.

327
00:21:41,690 --> 00:21:42,980
- See you, Woo Joo!
- Bye-bye!

328
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,361
Say goodbye.

329
00:21:44,361 --> 00:21:45,735
Say "I'll be back."

330
00:21:45,735 --> 00:21:46,863
Smile and bow.

331
00:21:46,863 --> 00:21:48,866
There you go!

332
00:21:51,618 --> 00:21:53,580
Let's go.

333
00:21:57,782 --> 00:22:00,460
I really appreciate this.

334
00:22:00,460 --> 00:22:02,420
You saved me from being late.

335
00:22:02,420 --> 00:22:04,965
The morning daycare run with Woo Joo
sounds exhausting.

336
00:22:04,965 --> 00:22:08,172
Yeah, the neighbor grandma has been our go-to,

337
00:22:08,172 --> 00:22:10,466
but she's out of commission for now.

338
00:22:10,466 --> 00:22:11,801
But what brought you here

339
00:22:11,801 --> 00:22:13,553
with no heads-up at all?

340
00:22:13,553 --> 00:22:14,804
Well...

341
00:22:14,804 --> 00:22:16,685
My morning freed up early,

342
00:22:16,685 --> 00:22:19,062
and you're right on my route.

343
00:22:19,062 --> 00:22:21,686
When does Woo Joo's daycare
ride situation get sorted out?

344
00:22:21,686 --> 00:22:23,608
Let me take care of it.

345
00:22:23,608 --> 00:22:24,647
Excuse me?

346
00:22:24,647 --> 00:22:26,607
No, I'm totally fine by myself.

347
00:22:26,607 --> 00:22:27,405
What's wrong?

348
00:22:27,405 --> 00:22:29,664
Just think of it as carpooling.

349
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:39,158
Am I putting you in a weird spot?

350
00:22:39,158 --> 00:22:40,455
What?

351
00:22:40,455 --> 00:22:43,708
That stings a little, but fair.

352
00:22:43,708 --> 00:22:44,876
But instead,

353
00:22:44,876 --> 00:22:47,211
if you need my help, just say so.

354
00:22:47,211 --> 00:22:49,179
That much is okay, right?

355
00:22:49,897 --> 00:22:51,215
Yeah.

356
00:22:51,215 --> 00:22:52,675
I will.

357
00:22:52,675 --> 00:22:54,522
Thank you.

358
00:23:03,436 --> 00:23:05,696
Wait, what am I looking at?

359
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:08,232
No way!

360
00:23:08,232 --> 00:23:09,659
What's up with him?

361
00:23:09,659 --> 00:23:10,739
What's going on?

362
00:23:10,739 --> 00:23:14,329
This thing we put up today
on the GloMarket site

363
00:23:14,329 --> 00:23:17,243
was gone within two hours flat.

364
00:23:17,243 --> 00:23:19,126
For real?

365
00:23:21,078 --> 00:23:23,623
Manager, did you see this?

366
00:23:23,623 --> 00:23:24,749
Yes.

367
00:23:24,749 --> 00:23:27,505
The folks over at GloMarket are loving it, too.

368
00:23:27,505 --> 00:23:29,128
They just reached out

369
00:23:29,128 --> 00:23:32,089
asking to lock down a timeline
for the next product rollout.

370
00:23:32,089 --> 00:23:34,717
Every sleepless night was worth it.

371
00:23:34,717 --> 00:23:36,306
Thank goodness.

372
00:23:36,306 --> 00:23:38,663
[Amy Choo's Weekly Routine]

373
00:23:38,663 --> 00:23:40,037
[Cold Buckwheat Noodles, Mido]

374
00:23:40,037 --> 00:23:40,871
[Roast and Grilled Meat]

375
00:23:40,871 --> 00:23:42,482
[Vine Salad, Osaka Tempura Rice Bowl]

376
00:23:45,704 --> 00:23:47,609
[Don't Forget Her Supplements]

377
00:23:47,609 --> 00:23:49,861
What's so crucial about this thing

378
00:23:49,861 --> 00:23:50,987
that he nagged me nonstop to read it?

379
00:23:50,987 --> 00:23:52,448
So I went ahead and looked it over,

380
00:23:52,448 --> 00:23:55,243
and is this some kind of transition file

381
00:23:55,243 --> 00:23:56,822
or a profile on his former wife?

382
00:23:56,822 --> 00:23:58,533
Found any good locations yet?

383
00:23:58,533 --> 00:24:00,660
No. I just haven't found

384
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:02,954
anything that really speaks to me,

385
00:24:02,954 --> 00:24:04,247
so I'm still looking around.

386
00:24:04,247 --> 00:24:06,532
Wait, shouldn't you be leaving now?

387
00:24:06,532 --> 00:24:08,334
Your BS interview is today, right?

388
00:24:08,334 --> 00:24:10,345
I know, I'm on my way out.

389
00:24:11,962 --> 00:24:15,090
You've really made it big,

390
00:24:15,090 --> 00:24:16,829
photographer Sun Tae Hyung!

391
00:24:16,829 --> 00:24:18,782
With your name out there and all.

392
00:24:18,782 --> 00:24:20,183
It's only an in-house publication.

393
00:24:20,183 --> 00:24:22,312
That's still a big deal.

394
00:24:22,312 --> 00:24:23,656
Wait.

395
00:24:23,656 --> 00:24:25,117
Don't you think we should pick up

396
00:24:25,117 --> 00:24:27,400
something for the manager's farewell?

397
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,444
That crossed my mind too,

398
00:24:29,444 --> 00:24:31,786
but I can't figure out what to buy.

399
00:24:50,255 --> 00:24:52,670
Hand over those vitamins you carried in.

400
00:24:52,670 --> 00:24:54,388
What?

401
00:24:57,704 --> 00:24:59,969
Oh, it's you.

402
00:24:59,969 --> 00:25:01,010
What's up?

403
00:25:01,010 --> 00:25:02,805
I've got the BS interview now

404
00:25:02,805 --> 00:25:04,348
and I'll leave right from there.

405
00:25:04,348 --> 00:25:06,111
Alright.

406
00:25:09,206 --> 00:25:10,275
By the way,

407
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:12,737
what does the manager like?

408
00:25:14,371 --> 00:25:16,317
What he likes?

409
00:25:16,317 --> 00:25:19,033
We're picking out a parting gift,

410
00:25:19,033 --> 00:25:21,621
but none of us know his taste.

411
00:25:22,325 --> 00:25:25,252
Well, he...

412
00:25:29,002 --> 00:25:30,017
Leave.

413
00:25:30,017 --> 00:25:31,929
I'm working right now.

414
00:25:35,152 --> 00:25:39,141
He's flying out to the States
on the 13th, a night flight.

415
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:42,803
Thought you might want to know.

416
00:25:42,803 --> 00:25:45,442
It could be some time before he's back.

417
00:25:47,153 --> 00:25:49,276
Just a heads up.

418
00:25:50,857 --> 00:25:52,735
I'm off then.

419
00:25:59,645 --> 00:26:01,646
America, out of nowhere?

420
00:26:17,036 --> 00:26:18,297
Oh, hold on.

421
00:26:18,297 --> 00:26:20,553
Watch out.

422
00:26:20,553 --> 00:26:22,514
Even a coffee maker can be dangerous.

423
00:26:22,514 --> 00:26:24,615
I'll handle that, alright?

424
00:26:24,615 --> 00:26:26,100
Amy Choo,

425
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:27,912
I know you prefer iced stuff,

426
00:26:27,912 --> 00:26:30,288
but try a hot one once in a while.

427
00:26:40,778 --> 00:26:42,334
Head in there and take a break.

428
00:26:42,334 --> 00:26:43,975
Even if it's just ten minutes,

429
00:26:43,975 --> 00:26:46,645
resting properly makes a difference.

430
00:26:46,645 --> 00:26:49,836
You need to take care of yourself.

431
00:27:01,271 --> 00:27:02,299
I spent way too much time

432
00:27:02,299 --> 00:27:04,560
hanging around Jo Moo Saeng.

433
00:27:16,903 --> 00:27:19,740
[Amy Choo's Weekly Routine]

434
00:27:24,784 --> 00:27:28,121
Five minutes in the microwave does the trick.

435
00:27:28,121 --> 00:27:29,874
Oh yeah?

436
00:27:31,454 --> 00:27:33,175
Over here.

437
00:27:46,842 --> 00:27:49,625
You heard the launch sold out, right?

438
00:27:49,625 --> 00:27:51,098
That's largely thanks to you.

439
00:27:51,098 --> 00:27:53,313
No way, the whole team earned this.

440
00:27:53,313 --> 00:27:55,728
Everyone's already gathered.

441
00:27:55,728 --> 00:27:57,913
- I'll show them the way.
- Okay.

442
00:27:57,913 --> 00:27:59,857
The interview room is just over there.

443
00:27:59,857 --> 00:28:01,275
As I said before,

444
00:28:01,275 --> 00:28:03,903
this is for the BS in-house magazine,

445
00:28:03,903 --> 00:28:05,654
so there's nothing to worry about.

446
00:28:05,654 --> 00:28:08,365
Just respond to my questions freely.

447
00:28:08,365 --> 00:28:10,295
Ready to dive in?

448
00:28:13,958 --> 00:28:16,296
Let's kick off the interview.

449
00:28:17,190 --> 00:28:19,746
The global market has always been

450
00:28:19,746 --> 00:28:22,004
the barrier BS couldn't overcome.

451
00:28:22,004 --> 00:28:25,594
And Planning Team 3 made it happen.

452
00:28:25,594 --> 00:28:29,057
Did you anticipate this kind of result
from the beginning?

453
00:28:29,057 --> 00:28:31,517
I never once thought we would fail.

454
00:28:31,517 --> 00:28:33,853
People kept telling me it would be hard

455
00:28:33,853 --> 00:28:36,015
because we had lost the chance before,

456
00:28:36,015 --> 00:28:38,149
but I saw it differently.

457
00:28:38,149 --> 00:28:40,606
I was confident
we would nail it this time around.

458
00:28:40,606 --> 00:28:44,197
That's exactly what we'd hear
from the youngest manager in BS history.

459
00:28:44,197 --> 00:28:46,201
It must feel so comforting

460
00:28:46,201 --> 00:28:48,072
to have a manager like him.

461
00:28:48,072 --> 00:28:49,822
Absolutely, because of him,

462
00:28:49,822 --> 00:28:52,705
I've picked up so much
and developed a lot in no time.

463
00:28:52,705 --> 00:28:53,744
That said,

464
00:28:53,744 --> 00:28:55,924
when he loaded me up with tasks,

465
00:28:55,924 --> 00:28:58,218
I did hold it against him a bit.

466
00:28:58,930 --> 00:29:00,630
Right, the GloMarket project

467
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:03,379
was your first since coming on board?

468
00:29:03,379 --> 00:29:05,499
That must have been quite a struggle.

469
00:29:05,499 --> 00:29:09,013
I'd love to hear how you handled
the difficult times.

470
00:29:09,013 --> 00:29:10,719
Rather than overcoming it,

471
00:29:10,719 --> 00:29:12,352
during those times,

472
00:29:12,352 --> 00:29:14,816
all I wanted was to head home.

473
00:29:14,816 --> 00:29:16,511
Get home,

474
00:29:16,511 --> 00:29:20,020
vent about how hard my day was,

475
00:29:20,020 --> 00:29:22,737
just let it all out crying...

476
00:29:22,737 --> 00:29:25,996
And weirdly, that would fix things.

477
00:29:35,703 --> 00:29:37,371
Okay, the next one is

478
00:29:37,371 --> 00:29:39,794
for Sun Tae Hyung.

479
00:29:39,794 --> 00:29:43,229
You led the visual direction on this one,

480
00:29:43,229 --> 00:29:45,810
and people online are loving it.

481
00:29:45,810 --> 00:29:49,373
From what I hear, you're diving
into another project with BS?

482
00:29:49,373 --> 00:29:51,302
That's right, I'm coming on board for something

483
00:29:51,302 --> 00:29:53,224
the marketing team is cooking up,

484
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:56,045
so we should have something cool
coming your way before long.

485
00:29:56,045 --> 00:29:58,021
Photography isn't really my area,

486
00:29:58,021 --> 00:29:59,226
but the shots you captured

487
00:29:59,226 --> 00:30:00,811
really struck a chord with me.

488
00:30:00,811 --> 00:30:02,608
Thank you.

489
00:30:02,608 --> 00:30:06,612
What drew you to photography?

490
00:30:06,612 --> 00:30:09,032
Initially, it was my brother's influence.

491
00:30:09,032 --> 00:30:11,257
He inspired me to grab a camera

492
00:30:11,257 --> 00:30:14,078
and start shooting.

493
00:30:14,078 --> 00:30:15,367
After a while, though,

494
00:30:15,367 --> 00:30:17,929
I walked away from it completely.

495
00:30:17,929 --> 00:30:22,048
I swore I was done with it for good,

496
00:30:22,794 --> 00:30:24,714
but part of me still ached for it

497
00:30:24,714 --> 00:30:27,176
and yearned to come back to it.

498
00:30:28,008 --> 00:30:30,303
Then somebody shared a thought with me.

499
00:30:30,303 --> 00:30:32,263
What did they tell you?

500
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:34,517
They said to go and confirm it myself.

501
00:30:35,308 --> 00:30:38,227
Whether I was clinging to regret

502
00:30:38,227 --> 00:30:41,247
or genuine love for it.

503
00:30:41,247 --> 00:30:44,867
There are emotions you can only grasp
by taking them to the finish line.

504
00:30:45,693 --> 00:30:48,529
So I returned to it,

505
00:30:48,529 --> 00:30:49,944
and everything became clear.

506
00:30:49,944 --> 00:30:52,666
How deep my passion runs for this.

507
00:30:53,743 --> 00:30:56,080
Had it not been for that person,

508
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:57,993
I likely never would have considered

509
00:30:57,993 --> 00:31:00,003
touching a camera again.

510
00:31:10,974 --> 00:31:12,303
Goodness.

511
00:31:12,303 --> 00:31:14,138
It's been such a long time.

512
00:31:14,138 --> 00:31:16,709
You moved so suddenly,

513
00:31:16,709 --> 00:31:19,807
you have no idea how worried we were.

514
00:31:19,807 --> 00:31:21,392
I apologize for that.

515
00:31:21,392 --> 00:31:23,459
That's just how things unfolded.

516
00:31:23,459 --> 00:31:24,857
Is your back holding up all right?

517
00:31:24,857 --> 00:31:26,511
It's okay.

518
00:31:26,511 --> 00:31:28,148
When you're as old as me,

519
00:31:28,148 --> 00:31:31,248
everything starts falling apart.

520
00:31:32,152 --> 00:31:33,153
Woo Joo,

521
00:31:33,153 --> 00:31:34,780
come over here to Grandma.

522
00:31:34,780 --> 00:31:37,008
- Go to Grandma.
- You're so cute.

523
00:31:37,995 --> 00:31:39,660
Goodness, look at this little one.

524
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:44,252
He's completely attached to his uncle.

525
00:31:44,252 --> 00:31:46,250
That reminds me.

526
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:48,377
Can you pull out some diapers

527
00:31:48,377 --> 00:31:50,421
for Woo Joo before you leave.

528
00:31:50,421 --> 00:31:51,454
Diapers?

529
00:31:51,454 --> 00:31:52,798
Hyun Jin mentioned

530
00:31:52,798 --> 00:31:56,427
she would share the door code with me.

531
00:31:56,427 --> 00:31:59,847
But I told her I'd ask you later.

532
00:31:59,847 --> 00:32:02,653
Oh, about that incident before...

533
00:32:04,340 --> 00:32:07,271
It did come up,

534
00:32:07,271 --> 00:32:12,321
and it's best not to start any rumors.

535
00:32:12,321 --> 00:32:15,702
Alright, Woo Joo, come here.

536
00:32:53,285 --> 00:32:56,206
Handling everything solo must be chaos.

537
00:33:07,919 --> 00:33:10,840
How am I supposed to wash or tidy up?

538
00:33:14,425 --> 00:33:16,990
Okay, let's head in.

539
00:33:16,990 --> 00:33:19,646
It's gotten so late today.

540
00:33:39,033 --> 00:33:42,574
You were out of rice, so I made a fresh batch.

541
00:33:42,574 --> 00:33:46,749
Even when things get crazy,
don't skip your meals.

542
00:33:46,749 --> 00:33:49,377
Woo Joo, open wide.

543
00:33:49,377 --> 00:33:50,916
That's it, what a good eater.

544
00:33:50,916 --> 00:33:53,627
Okay, time to dig in.

545
00:33:53,627 --> 00:33:54,878
I appreciate it.

546
00:33:54,878 --> 00:33:57,178
It's burning.

547
00:33:57,178 --> 00:33:58,799
Be careful.

548
00:33:58,799 --> 00:34:00,801
Here.

549
00:34:00,801 --> 00:34:04,691
I swore I was done with it for good,

550
00:34:05,556 --> 00:34:07,474
but part of me still ached for it

551
00:34:07,474 --> 00:34:09,685
and yearned to come back to it.

552
00:34:09,685 --> 00:34:11,311
Then somebody shared a thought with me.

553
00:34:11,311 --> 00:34:13,188
They said to go and confirm it myself.

554
00:34:13,188 --> 00:34:16,066
Whether I was clinging to regret

555
00:34:16,066 --> 00:34:18,497
or genuine love for it.

556
00:34:22,489 --> 00:34:25,333
He actually made rice and then took off.

557
00:34:44,932 --> 00:34:47,906
Woo Joo, let's eat some broccoli.

558
00:34:50,313 --> 00:34:52,317
You don't want it?

559
00:34:52,317 --> 00:34:54,371
Then should I give it to Uncle?

560
00:34:59,276 --> 00:35:01,953
Yeah?

561
00:35:03,451 --> 00:35:06,044
There you go, eating so well.

562
00:35:23,552 --> 00:35:26,440
I wonder if she's been
keeping up with her meals...

563
00:35:32,063 --> 00:35:33,810
This is the one, right? Your dream item.

564
00:35:35,604 --> 00:35:38,482
It looks even better on you in real life.

565
00:35:38,482 --> 00:35:40,692
What are we doing here all of a sudden?

566
00:35:40,692 --> 00:35:41,693
What do you think?

567
00:35:41,693 --> 00:35:43,695
Excuse me, do you have this in stock?

568
00:35:43,695 --> 00:35:45,242
No, no, it's fine.

569
00:35:45,242 --> 00:35:46,369
What are you talking about?

570
00:35:46,369 --> 00:35:48,456
It's a housewarming present.

571
00:35:49,201 --> 00:35:50,619
If you're worried about the price,

572
00:35:50,619 --> 00:35:51,370
I'll go ahead and get it

573
00:35:51,370 --> 00:35:54,831
and tear it open myself, so just accept it.

574
00:35:54,831 --> 00:35:56,705
No, it's not about that.

575
00:35:56,705 --> 00:35:57,709
It's a safety issue.

576
00:35:57,709 --> 00:35:59,336
What if there's a fall

577
00:35:59,336 --> 00:36:00,712
or a crash from racing around?

578
00:36:00,712 --> 00:36:02,005
When would you ever fall or run into

579
00:36:02,005 --> 00:36:03,382
something in your own place?

580
00:36:03,382 --> 00:36:05,545
I meant Woo Joo, not me.

581
00:36:05,545 --> 00:36:08,136
The moment you take your eyes off him,
he's darting around everywhere.

582
00:36:08,136 --> 00:36:09,471
Imagine if he tore himself on this.

583
00:36:09,471 --> 00:36:11,985
Glass like this is seriously hazardous.

584
00:36:12,978 --> 00:36:14,899
I appreciate the thought.

585
00:36:16,270 --> 00:36:18,150
What do you think of this one?

586
00:36:18,150 --> 00:36:19,168
That looks great on you.

587
00:36:19,168 --> 00:36:20,524
Try it on.

588
00:36:20,524 --> 00:36:21,525
Should I?

589
00:36:21,525 --> 00:36:22,484
How about you?

590
00:36:22,484 --> 00:36:23,739
Spot anything that catches your eye?

591
00:36:23,739 --> 00:36:25,862
You always like the stuff here.

592
00:36:25,862 --> 00:36:27,114
I want to browse a little longer.

593
00:36:27,114 --> 00:36:28,919
Go put it on already.

594
00:36:48,441 --> 00:36:50,427
Where did he go?

595
00:36:58,645 --> 00:37:00,556
This would be adorable.

596
00:37:02,361 --> 00:37:04,609
When was the last time
the two of us hung out like this?

597
00:37:04,609 --> 00:37:05,902
Tell me about it.

598
00:37:05,902 --> 00:37:08,746
Even if it's just a kids' cafe.

599
00:37:09,698 --> 00:37:10,615
Right.

600
00:37:10,615 --> 00:37:12,921
Is Tae Hyung not at home today?

601
00:37:15,006 --> 00:37:16,246
We're not staying together now.

602
00:37:16,246 --> 00:37:18,123
Wait, how come?

603
00:37:18,123 --> 00:37:19,666
I mean, obviously.

604
00:37:19,666 --> 00:37:21,922
The renovation is finished.

605
00:37:21,922 --> 00:37:23,299
Oh, that's right.

606
00:37:23,299 --> 00:37:24,588
He was only living with you

607
00:37:24,588 --> 00:37:25,839
while the renovations wrapped up, right?

608
00:37:25,839 --> 00:37:29,020
You both hit it off so nicely,
I completely forgot about that.

609
00:37:33,829 --> 00:37:35,454
Are you free tomorrow?

610
00:37:35,454 --> 00:37:38,685
We've still got one more date to go.

611
00:37:38,685 --> 00:37:40,479
Let's go somewhere together.

612
00:37:40,479 --> 00:37:42,564
Who's that?

613
00:37:42,564 --> 00:37:44,649
It's Yoon Seong.

614
00:37:44,649 --> 00:37:45,760
Hey, speaking of which,

615
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:47,319
how did things turn out with the date

616
00:37:47,319 --> 00:37:49,446
you had planned with him?

617
00:37:49,446 --> 00:37:51,323
Funny you bring that up.

618
00:37:51,323 --> 00:37:53,533
There's still one remaining.

619
00:37:53,533 --> 00:37:56,180
Have you figured out how you feel?

620
00:37:56,180 --> 00:37:58,997
It seems like he takes really good care of you.

621
00:37:58,997 --> 00:38:01,654
I truly appreciate it,

622
00:38:01,654 --> 00:38:04,086
but it sits heavy on my chest.

623
00:38:04,086 --> 00:38:05,629
So he treats you well,

624
00:38:05,629 --> 00:38:08,160
and yet it feels like a burden?

625
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:09,204
How come?

626
00:38:09,204 --> 00:38:11,646
I feel guilty about it,

627
00:38:12,386 --> 00:38:14,971
and slightly uneasy too.

628
00:38:14,971 --> 00:38:17,317
I can't quite explain it clearly,

629
00:38:17,317 --> 00:38:19,480
but somewhere along the way,

630
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:20,560
every kind thing from him

631
00:38:20,560 --> 00:38:23,067
began weighing on me

632
00:38:23,067 --> 00:38:25,444
as if I'm in his debt.

633
00:38:25,444 --> 00:38:27,317
That tells you everything right there.

634
00:38:27,317 --> 00:38:28,030
What are you saying?

635
00:38:28,030 --> 00:38:31,238
When it's a person you care about,
being kind to you,

636
00:38:31,238 --> 00:38:33,281
it brings comfort, not pressure.

637
00:38:33,281 --> 00:38:34,282
However,

638
00:38:34,282 --> 00:38:36,868
when a person you're not into treats you well,

639
00:38:36,868 --> 00:38:38,995
it becomes a weight on your shoulders.

640
00:38:38,995 --> 00:38:40,288
And the reason is simple.

641
00:38:40,288 --> 00:38:43,261
It's because that kind of feeling
isn't something you can return.

642
00:38:44,801 --> 00:38:46,173
Even so,

643
00:38:46,173 --> 00:38:48,130
you should follow through on that date.

644
00:38:48,130 --> 00:38:50,298
Remember what Tae Hyung said?

645
00:38:50,298 --> 00:38:51,508
There are emotions you can only grasp

646
00:38:51,508 --> 00:38:53,938
by taking them to the finish line.

647
00:39:02,940 --> 00:39:04,667
This house...

648
00:39:04,667 --> 00:39:07,697
Does this actually belong to you?

649
00:39:07,697 --> 00:39:09,363
Right.

650
00:39:09,363 --> 00:39:11,841
It's pretty jarring, to be honest.

651
00:39:11,841 --> 00:39:14,285
Wait, this taste...

652
00:39:14,285 --> 00:39:16,011
Are you serious right now?

653
00:39:16,011 --> 00:39:18,880
What? It's perfectly nice.

654
00:39:22,918 --> 00:39:25,963
But really, what happened to you?

655
00:39:25,963 --> 00:39:27,940
You were always so passionate about decor.

656
00:39:27,940 --> 00:39:30,276
All that "my own sacred sanctuary" talk
and whatnot.

657
00:39:30,276 --> 00:39:32,361
My preferences just evolved,

658
00:39:32,361 --> 00:39:35,030
from idealistic to functional.

659
00:39:35,030 --> 00:39:36,640
No, you're acting different.

660
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:37,908
Other stuff aside,

661
00:39:37,908 --> 00:39:39,618
when it came to your own space,

662
00:39:39,618 --> 00:39:41,020
you were crazy about your belongings.

663
00:39:41,020 --> 00:39:41,812
That's what I'm saying.

664
00:39:41,812 --> 00:39:43,456
Back at the mall,

665
00:39:43,456 --> 00:39:47,042
you skipped right past your own stuff
and only checked out baby outfits.

666
00:39:47,042 --> 00:39:49,670
You're like a whole different person.

667
00:39:49,670 --> 00:39:51,755
Oh, stop it.

668
00:39:51,755 --> 00:39:53,507
Hey, what about getting a fountain pen

669
00:39:53,507 --> 00:39:55,009
as a farewell present for the manager?

670
00:39:55,009 --> 00:39:56,472
A fountain pen.

671
00:39:56,472 --> 00:39:57,703
That's a pretty standard pick.

672
00:39:57,703 --> 00:39:58,721
Hold on, why is he quitting?

673
00:39:58,721 --> 00:40:00,473
The manager is resigning?

674
00:40:00,473 --> 00:40:01,999
Isn't he Amy Choo's husband?

675
00:40:01,999 --> 00:40:05,269
Actually, he's her ex-husband now.

676
00:40:05,269 --> 00:40:06,395
The two of them split up.

677
00:40:06,395 --> 00:40:08,147
So he stepped away from work as well.

678
00:40:08,147 --> 00:40:10,524
Your workplace must be tense right now.

679
00:40:10,524 --> 00:40:12,595
I expected that too,

680
00:40:12,595 --> 00:40:14,111
but to my surprise,

681
00:40:14,111 --> 00:40:15,571
she appears completely unbothered.

682
00:40:15,571 --> 00:40:17,731
She genuinely seems to be doing well.

683
00:40:18,741 --> 00:40:22,610
She could just be putting on a brave face
from the surface.

684
00:40:23,228 --> 00:40:25,372
True, that's possible.

685
00:40:25,372 --> 00:40:27,374
Honestly, seeing the two of them

686
00:40:27,374 --> 00:40:29,376
drives me crazy.

687
00:40:29,376 --> 00:40:32,821
The manager obviously still cares about her.

688
00:40:32,821 --> 00:40:35,007
If his feelings were that strong,
why did he walk away, you know?

689
00:40:35,007 --> 00:40:37,176
He should have pleaded, "Pay attention to me.

690
00:40:37,176 --> 00:40:38,719
I need to stay close to you."

691
00:40:38,719 --> 00:40:39,956
He should have fought for her,

692
00:40:39,956 --> 00:40:42,046
instead of leaving.

693
00:40:43,791 --> 00:40:45,958
He likely thought his presence

694
00:40:45,958 --> 00:40:48,756
would only make things worse.

695
00:40:48,756 --> 00:40:50,314
That's exactly the problem.

696
00:40:50,314 --> 00:40:53,258
Why does he make that call by himself
without consulting anyone?

697
00:40:53,258 --> 00:40:55,986
They need to talk it out.

698
00:40:55,986 --> 00:40:58,389
And having family around

699
00:40:58,389 --> 00:41:00,349
is a hundred times better than not.

700
00:41:00,349 --> 00:41:01,992
Seung Taek has a point there.

701
00:41:01,992 --> 00:41:04,203
It's not about what you can do.

702
00:41:04,203 --> 00:41:06,355
Simply showing up means everything.

703
00:41:06,355 --> 00:41:07,915
That's the whole point of family.

704
00:41:07,915 --> 00:41:09,458
As you go through life,

705
00:41:09,458 --> 00:41:12,834
very few people actually feel
like real family to you.

706
00:41:12,834 --> 00:41:15,297
If you find someone like that,
hold on to them no matter what.

707
00:41:15,297 --> 00:41:17,349
My thoughts exactly.

708
00:41:18,132 --> 00:41:19,134
I just hope she would

709
00:41:19,134 --> 00:41:21,711
make an effort to keep the manager.

710
00:41:34,984 --> 00:41:38,445
He's flying out to the States
on the 13th, a night flight.

711
00:41:38,445 --> 00:41:41,105
It could be some time before he's back.

712
00:41:50,061 --> 00:41:53,952
How could you wait until now to say that?

713
00:41:54,878 --> 00:41:56,463
Okay, I hear you.

714
00:41:56,463 --> 00:41:58,048
I just got to work,

715
00:41:58,048 --> 00:42:00,259
so I'll look into it and get back to you.

716
00:42:00,259 --> 00:42:02,511
Got it.

717
00:42:02,511 --> 00:42:05,372
Should've told me sooner if it was this urgent.

718
00:42:05,372 --> 00:42:08,545
Of all days, on my precious weekend.

719
00:42:15,966 --> 00:42:18,110
What brings you here on a weekend?

720
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:20,863
A last-minute meeting popped up.

721
00:42:20,863 --> 00:42:22,100
What about you?

722
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:25,400
I had an emergency situation as well.

723
00:42:27,745 --> 00:42:29,772
Well...

724
00:42:29,772 --> 00:42:32,073
Have you looked up at the sky today?

725
00:42:33,358 --> 00:42:35,613
It's absolutely gorgeous out.

726
00:42:37,191 --> 00:42:38,530
Why on earth

727
00:42:38,530 --> 00:42:41,452
do we have to be working on such a perfect day?

728
00:42:45,496 --> 00:42:46,597
- Yeah.
- Hey.

729
00:42:46,597 --> 00:42:48,641
When does the manager's plane leave?

730
00:42:48,641 --> 00:42:50,717
It's an evening flight.

731
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:55,839
Every flight to the States goes out at night.

732
00:42:55,839 --> 00:42:56,924
Right.

733
00:42:56,924 --> 00:42:58,675
After I wrap up the meeting,
I'll swing by the studio

734
00:42:58,675 --> 00:43:00,638
and leave right after.

735
00:43:01,443 --> 00:43:04,181
I need to arrive with extra time
to drop off my luggage.

736
00:43:04,181 --> 00:43:05,324
The States?

737
00:43:05,324 --> 00:43:07,868
So will there be enough time
to pick up a present?

738
00:43:07,868 --> 00:43:09,328
I checked and there's a shop

739
00:43:09,328 --> 00:43:11,013
that carries fountain pens.

740
00:43:11,013 --> 00:43:13,907
I'll just buy it there on the way.

741
00:43:19,113 --> 00:43:22,407
Is he moving there for good?

742
00:43:22,407 --> 00:43:24,537
In the U.S.?

743
00:43:26,787 --> 00:43:28,496
It's Uncle!

744
00:43:28,496 --> 00:43:30,840
There's Uncle!

745
00:43:32,643 --> 00:43:33,913
Uncle!

746
00:43:33,913 --> 00:43:35,704
It's Uncle!

747
00:43:35,704 --> 00:43:38,640
- Uncle!
- Uncle!

748
00:43:39,329 --> 00:43:40,484
Uncle.

749
00:43:40,484 --> 00:43:42,945
Have you been good?

750
00:43:42,945 --> 00:43:45,938
- Uncle.
- Uncle.

751
00:43:50,369 --> 00:43:52,820
Congrats on your first day of school.

752
00:43:54,157 --> 00:43:56,491
Seo Yoon, this is what you wished for?

753
00:43:57,835 --> 00:43:59,577
Chan Woo, it's for you.

754
00:44:01,282 --> 00:44:03,289
And lastly, here you go.

755
00:44:04,491 --> 00:44:06,301
You must be so busy.

756
00:44:06,301 --> 00:44:08,120
You don't have to come every time.

757
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:10,180
Oh, please don't talk like that.

758
00:44:10,180 --> 00:44:11,640
I'm not busy at all.

759
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:13,559
I'm just grateful, that's all.

760
00:44:13,559 --> 00:44:17,136
And who might this be?

761
00:44:18,515 --> 00:44:22,151
Hello. I went to school with Yoon Seong.

762
00:44:22,151 --> 00:44:24,987
And now we're at the same company.

763
00:44:24,987 --> 00:44:27,313
Oh, I see.

764
00:44:27,906 --> 00:44:30,951
You two have quite the history together.

765
00:44:30,951 --> 00:44:32,453
I appreciate you being here.

766
00:44:32,453 --> 00:44:34,329
Have the kids had anything to eat?

767
00:44:34,329 --> 00:44:35,706
Not yet.

768
00:44:35,706 --> 00:44:37,207
They've been counting down to this

769
00:44:37,207 --> 00:44:38,859
for the past few days.

770
00:44:38,859 --> 00:44:40,502
- Pizza, chicken!
- Pizza, chicken!

771
00:44:40,502 --> 00:44:45,132
- Chicken, chicken!
- Chicken, chicken!

772
00:44:45,132 --> 00:44:47,509
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

773
00:44:47,509 --> 00:44:49,293
Enjoy.

774
00:44:50,888 --> 00:44:52,959
I thought you'd cook for them.

775
00:44:52,959 --> 00:44:54,628
I gave it a shot before,

776
00:44:54,628 --> 00:44:56,129
but with children this young,

777
00:44:56,129 --> 00:44:58,103
takeout wins every time.

778
00:44:58,103 --> 00:44:59,772
Yeah, that's fair enough.

779
00:44:59,772 --> 00:45:00,898
Excuse me.

780
00:45:00,898 --> 00:45:02,886
- Yeah?
- This is for you.

781
00:45:02,886 --> 00:45:05,843
- You're giving this to me?
- Yes.

782
00:45:05,843 --> 00:45:06,862
Thank you.

783
00:45:06,862 --> 00:45:07,931
What about me?

784
00:45:07,931 --> 00:45:09,890
You don't need milk.

785
00:45:09,890 --> 00:45:12,520
You're tall enough already.

786
00:45:14,745 --> 00:45:15,996
Thank you for this.

787
00:45:15,996 --> 00:45:17,873
It's way better while it's still hot.

788
00:45:17,873 --> 00:45:19,458
Come over here to eat.

789
00:45:19,458 --> 00:45:20,459
Have a seat right here.

790
00:45:20,459 --> 00:45:22,410
Sit down and start eating.

791
00:45:24,046 --> 00:45:26,632
When you hold it this way,
your fingers don't get messy.

792
00:45:42,439 --> 00:45:43,565
Wait, what is...

793
00:45:43,565 --> 00:45:46,184
You finished all of this on your own?

794
00:45:46,777 --> 00:45:48,403
Oh, you're here?

795
00:45:48,403 --> 00:45:49,721
Care for a drink?

796
00:45:49,721 --> 00:45:51,073
I'm good.

797
00:45:51,073 --> 00:45:53,058
How much did you even drink?

798
00:45:53,058 --> 00:45:54,993
A bottle or two?

799
00:45:54,993 --> 00:45:57,270
No, maybe three?

800
00:45:57,270 --> 00:45:58,370
So what?

801
00:45:58,370 --> 00:46:00,995
No matter how much I drink, I can't get drunk.

802
00:46:00,995 --> 00:46:03,743
You look plenty drunk to me.

803
00:46:04,860 --> 00:46:07,038
That can't be right.

804
00:46:07,038 --> 00:46:11,375
If I were drunk,
I wouldn't keep seeing Jo Moo Saeng.

805
00:46:12,604 --> 00:46:15,389
Oh, you're wasted.

806
00:46:15,389 --> 00:46:17,381
On your feet, let's move.

807
00:46:18,291 --> 00:46:20,004
For what?

808
00:46:20,669 --> 00:46:22,370
What do you mean, for what?

809
00:46:22,370 --> 00:46:24,501
You have to make it to the airport.

810
00:46:24,501 --> 00:46:26,253
What reason do I have to go there?

811
00:46:26,253 --> 00:46:29,069
This is all because of the manager.

812
00:46:29,069 --> 00:46:32,447
I'll drive you, so go after him.

813
00:46:32,447 --> 00:46:34,248
Don't bother.

814
00:46:35,367 --> 00:46:37,661
We've already passed the point of return.

815
00:46:37,661 --> 00:46:40,539
Go catch him before the chance is gone.

816
00:46:40,539 --> 00:46:42,649
From the moment the manager resigned,

817
00:46:42,649 --> 00:46:44,751
you have not been the same.

818
00:46:44,751 --> 00:46:46,127
His absence leaves a hole in you,

819
00:46:46,127 --> 00:46:48,919
he's constantly on your mind,
and you long to see him.

820
00:46:49,923 --> 00:46:52,083
So why are you letting him walk away?

821
00:46:52,742 --> 00:46:55,586
[Amy Choo's Favorites List]

822
00:46:56,471 --> 00:46:58,306
I came across this.

823
00:46:58,306 --> 00:47:00,615
He truly understood

824
00:47:00,615 --> 00:47:03,979
every single detail about me,

825
00:47:03,979 --> 00:47:06,314
inside and out.

826
00:47:06,314 --> 00:47:07,816
Yet

827
00:47:07,816 --> 00:47:10,110
I had no clue about anything

828
00:47:10,110 --> 00:47:12,061
that mattered to him.

829
00:47:12,946 --> 00:47:15,856
I never truly gave back to him.

830
00:47:18,453 --> 00:47:20,903
What right do I have to keep him?

831
00:47:49,424 --> 00:47:54,487
[Giving Dreams and Love to Children]

832
00:47:54,487 --> 00:47:56,698
She hasn't been here long.

833
00:47:56,698 --> 00:47:59,125
She was previously with her family,

834
00:47:59,125 --> 00:48:01,128
but her mother had circumstances arise

835
00:48:01,128 --> 00:48:03,788
and left her here suddenly.

836
00:48:03,788 --> 00:48:06,574
It will take her a while to settle in.

837
00:48:07,292 --> 00:48:08,877
Even so,

838
00:48:08,877 --> 00:48:10,879
refusing to eat like that...

839
00:48:10,879 --> 00:48:14,674
Children who grew up in a home

840
00:48:14,674 --> 00:48:17,260
struggle the most during mealtimes.

841
00:48:17,260 --> 00:48:18,762
That's understandable.

842
00:48:18,762 --> 00:48:22,923
It's nothing like sitting together
around the dinner table at home.

843
00:48:24,601 --> 00:48:26,510
Ji Ho.

844
00:48:29,272 --> 00:48:31,633
Ji Ho.

845
00:48:31,633 --> 00:48:32,984
Why are you out here by yourself?

846
00:48:32,984 --> 00:48:35,853
I'm waiting for my mom.

847
00:48:36,613 --> 00:48:40,700
I remember longing and waiting for someone

848
00:48:40,700 --> 00:48:43,652
so intensely,

849
00:48:44,514 --> 00:48:46,873
but my expectations were never

850
00:48:46,873 --> 00:48:49,074
once met.

851
00:48:53,546 --> 00:48:56,049
[Sunshine Bridge Children's Home]
Everyone's enjoying their food.

852
00:48:56,049 --> 00:48:56,867
Let's go inside.

853
00:48:56,867 --> 00:48:58,593
What's wrong? Let's eat pizza.

854
00:48:58,593 --> 00:48:59,761
Let's go in.

855
00:48:59,761 --> 00:49:02,504
Ji Ho is here.

856
00:49:03,162 --> 00:49:04,787
Have a seat right here.

857
00:49:04,787 --> 00:49:06,467
Here, eat this.

858
00:49:11,995 --> 00:49:13,891
Did you get something to eat?

859
00:49:18,405 --> 00:49:22,200
In your opinion, what makes the perfect meal?

860
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:25,704
Truth is, I've never been someone
who pays much attention to food.

861
00:49:25,704 --> 00:49:27,497
To me, a meal was

862
00:49:27,497 --> 00:49:29,416
nothing more than fuel.

863
00:49:29,416 --> 00:49:31,318
Frankly,

864
00:49:31,318 --> 00:49:33,495
I always thought those
who treated eating like some grand event

865
00:49:33,495 --> 00:49:35,714
were overreacting.

866
00:49:35,714 --> 00:49:37,831
And yet,

867
00:49:39,843 --> 00:49:42,137
somewhere along the way,

868
00:49:42,137 --> 00:49:44,672
I found myself acting the same way.

869
00:49:45,682 --> 00:49:49,310
When they skipped their morning meal,
it bothered me.

870
00:49:49,310 --> 00:49:50,937
[You were out of rice, so I made a fresh batch]
When they mentioned running late,

871
00:49:50,937 --> 00:49:54,390
I'd wonder if they were
taking care of themselves.

872
00:49:55,066 --> 00:49:58,769
Sitting down to eat together
turned into a form of reconciliation.

873
00:49:59,660 --> 00:50:02,189
Other days, it brought solace.

874
00:50:03,116 --> 00:50:05,493
That kind of warmth passing back and forth,

875
00:50:05,493 --> 00:50:07,820
I believe that's the heart of a meal.

876
00:50:09,164 --> 00:50:11,666
So the finest meal, in my eyes,

877
00:50:11,666 --> 00:50:13,592
has nothing to do with the dish.

878
00:50:15,098 --> 00:50:18,289
It's about the person across from you.

879
00:50:21,801 --> 00:50:24,937
Here, your friend gave you this.

880
00:50:31,102 --> 00:50:33,887
Let me step out for a phone call.

881
00:50:41,390 --> 00:50:42,405
It's me.

882
00:50:42,405 --> 00:50:43,948
Hyun Jin, I apologize.

883
00:50:43,948 --> 00:50:45,784
I know it's frustrating to get work calls

884
00:50:45,784 --> 00:50:46,977
on the weekend,

885
00:50:46,977 --> 00:50:48,828
but this is really urgent, so I had to call.

886
00:50:48,828 --> 00:50:50,036
Well...

887
00:50:50,036 --> 00:50:53,958
That HMR market analysis report you prepared?

888
00:50:53,958 --> 00:50:55,835
Where did you end up putting it?

889
00:50:55,835 --> 00:50:59,113
I printed it out
and placed it on the manager's desk.

890
00:50:59,113 --> 00:51:01,925
Oh, there it is.

891
00:51:01,925 --> 00:51:03,676
I appreciate it.

892
00:51:03,676 --> 00:51:05,887
Please say you're not in the office.

893
00:51:05,887 --> 00:51:08,787
Yeah, I'm pathetic, right?

894
00:51:08,787 --> 00:51:10,391
Seems like you're outside.

895
00:51:10,391 --> 00:51:13,311
Everyone's off enjoying life except me.

896
00:51:13,311 --> 00:51:15,980
One person is even heading to America.

897
00:51:15,980 --> 00:51:17,398
Who's leaving for the States?

898
00:51:17,398 --> 00:51:20,026
Sun Tae Hyung.

899
00:51:20,026 --> 00:51:22,278
Excuse me? Tae Hyung?

900
00:51:22,278 --> 00:51:24,906
He's your in-law, and you had no idea?

901
00:51:24,906 --> 00:51:26,908
Oh, maybe that's the reason.

902
00:51:26,908 --> 00:51:28,034
From what I heard,

903
00:51:28,034 --> 00:51:31,079
he might just stay there for good.

904
00:51:31,079 --> 00:51:33,123
Wait a second.

905
00:51:33,123 --> 00:51:35,625
Is that definitely true?

906
00:51:35,625 --> 00:51:37,502
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

907
00:51:37,502 --> 00:51:38,753
I'm telling you, it's true.

908
00:51:38,753 --> 00:51:40,839
His flight leaves tonight.

909
00:51:40,839 --> 00:51:43,098
He should be at the airport already.

910
00:51:52,976 --> 00:51:54,435
So

911
00:51:54,435 --> 00:51:57,814
how long has this been going on?

912
00:51:57,814 --> 00:51:58,940
What do you mean?

913
00:51:58,940 --> 00:52:01,617
Things weren't like this from the start.

914
00:52:02,652 --> 00:52:05,196
Having feelings for one another

915
00:52:05,196 --> 00:52:07,206
yet acting like you don't,

916
00:52:08,491 --> 00:52:10,876
keeping your real emotions locked away.

917
00:52:13,413 --> 00:52:17,292
That's so far back, I barely remember.

918
00:52:17,292 --> 00:52:20,712
"I miss you. I'm worried about you,"

919
00:52:20,712 --> 00:52:23,580
even those basic phrases felt impossible.

920
00:52:24,340 --> 00:52:26,509
Without realizing it,

921
00:52:26,509 --> 00:52:30,546
fear crept in.

922
00:52:31,431 --> 00:52:35,602
So I came up with reasons
over situations that were never real

923
00:52:35,602 --> 00:52:39,230
and continued shutting him out.

924
00:52:39,230 --> 00:52:41,482
If I'm being truthful,

925
00:52:41,482 --> 00:52:44,847
a piece of me wished

926
00:52:44,847 --> 00:52:46,979
he would stay.

927
00:52:49,574 --> 00:52:51,743
I believe I get

928
00:52:51,743 --> 00:52:53,907
what that's like.

929
00:52:56,022 --> 00:52:59,083
Feeling afraid without cause,

930
00:52:59,083 --> 00:53:01,135
lacking self-assurance,

931
00:53:02,674 --> 00:53:06,685
believing you should keep your distance.

932
00:53:07,759 --> 00:53:09,624
Sun Tae Hyung,

933
00:53:10,428 --> 00:53:13,589
I let it all slip and I'm paying for it.

934
00:53:15,074 --> 00:53:17,801
Grab on before it's too late.

935
00:53:23,942 --> 00:53:25,360
Where did you park?

936
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:26,819
What do you want with my car?

937
00:53:26,819 --> 00:53:28,071
Come on, stand up.

938
00:53:28,071 --> 00:53:29,906
I told you I'm staying put!

939
00:53:29,906 --> 00:53:31,199
You should go. Let's move.

940
00:53:31,199 --> 00:53:32,642
Careful, watch your step.

941
00:53:32,642 --> 00:53:34,619
Why would I go there?

942
00:53:34,619 --> 00:53:35,787
Don't look back with regret. Just go.

943
00:53:35,787 --> 00:53:38,790
And fix your makeup quickly.

944
00:53:38,790 --> 00:53:40,124
Hey!

945
00:53:40,124 --> 00:53:43,628
You should've told me I look like this!

946
00:53:43,628 --> 00:53:45,078
Why are you taking it out on me...

947
00:53:45,078 --> 00:53:46,339
Get in. Come on,

948
00:53:46,339 --> 00:53:48,999
Get in. Watch your head.

949
00:54:11,531 --> 00:54:13,574
Kind of dull, huh?

950
00:54:13,574 --> 00:54:15,285
Sorry?

951
00:54:15,285 --> 00:54:16,411
Not at all.

952
00:54:16,411 --> 00:54:17,912
How about we go in for a moment?

953
00:54:17,912 --> 00:54:19,664
There's actually something I want you to see.

954
00:54:19,664 --> 00:54:21,240
Okay.

955
00:54:26,713 --> 00:54:28,423
I think it's raining.

956
00:54:28,423 --> 00:54:30,537
Kids, the rain started. Head inside.

957
00:54:30,537 --> 00:54:31,579
It's raining.

958
00:54:31,579 --> 00:54:33,418
Let's go inside.

959
00:54:37,348 --> 00:54:39,642
If it's just this much rain,

960
00:54:39,642 --> 00:54:41,936
I don't mind

961
00:54:41,936 --> 00:54:45,013
getting soaked with you.

962
00:54:45,732 --> 00:54:47,900
I may not be your umbrella,

963
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:51,112
but at least until the rain falling on you

964
00:54:51,112 --> 00:54:52,530
finally stops,

965
00:54:52,530 --> 00:54:54,324
I can stay by your side.

966
00:54:54,324 --> 00:54:57,285
What is it? Talk to me.

967
00:54:57,285 --> 00:54:59,319
I feel safe now.

968
00:55:01,039 --> 00:55:04,292
When it's a person you care about,
being kind to you,

969
00:55:04,292 --> 00:55:07,035
it brings comfort, not pressure.

970
00:55:08,212 --> 00:55:11,035
Hyun Jin, are you okay?

971
00:55:11,035 --> 00:55:13,538
I have to leave right now.

972
00:55:13,538 --> 00:55:14,552
Where?

973
00:55:14,552 --> 00:55:17,221
I'll call you later.

974
00:55:17,221 --> 00:55:18,890
I'm sorry.

975
00:55:18,890 --> 00:55:20,725
But

976
00:55:20,725 --> 00:55:22,843
I really have to go.

977
00:55:36,593 --> 00:55:38,159
- Let me off here, please.
- Sure.

978
00:55:38,159 --> 00:55:40,110
Thank you.

979
00:55:48,147 --> 00:55:49,629
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

980
00:55:49,629 --> 00:55:51,339
Your call will be forwarded
to a voice message service.

981
00:55:51,339 --> 00:55:53,533
Fees may apply once connected,

982
00:55:53,533 --> 00:55:55,587
so if you prefer not to...

983
00:55:57,036 --> 00:55:58,471
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

984
00:55:58,471 --> 00:55:59,972
Your call will be forwarded
to a voice message service.

985
00:55:59,972 --> 00:56:01,474
When are they going to finish talking?

986
00:56:01,474 --> 00:56:04,852
Fees may apply once connected...

987
00:56:04,852 --> 00:56:07,980
Who is she even talking to for this long?

988
00:56:07,980 --> 00:56:09,107
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

989
00:56:09,107 --> 00:56:11,776
Who in the world is he talking to?

990
00:56:11,776 --> 00:56:14,682
There's no way he's gone yet, right?

991
00:56:14,682 --> 00:56:16,521
This can't be happening.

992
00:56:33,297 --> 00:56:35,540
Hyun Jin, where are you right now?

993
00:56:43,933 --> 00:56:45,807
Tae Hyung.

994
00:56:53,416 --> 00:56:54,944
Please stay.

995
00:56:54,944 --> 00:56:56,988
Don't go.

996
00:56:56,988 --> 00:57:00,450
How could you leave without saying anything?

997
00:57:00,450 --> 00:57:02,859
I refuse to send you off this way.

998
00:57:03,494 --> 00:57:05,078
Wait, you've got it wrong...

999
00:57:05,078 --> 00:57:06,863
I like you.

1000
00:57:08,869 --> 00:57:10,951
I like you, Tae Hyung.

1001
00:57:12,503 --> 00:57:14,489
That goes for me too.

1002
00:57:14,489 --> 00:57:16,199
Whether you were having proper meals

1003
00:57:16,199 --> 00:57:18,468
or going without food,

1004
00:57:18,468 --> 00:57:20,585
you were on my mind every day.

1005
00:57:21,204 --> 00:57:22,638
The spot where we once shared meals

1006
00:57:22,638 --> 00:57:25,257
felt so hollow without you.

1007
00:57:27,435 --> 00:57:29,886
That's why I kept thinking of you,

1008
00:57:31,439 --> 00:57:33,740
since you were gone.

1009
00:57:36,736 --> 00:57:37,778
Hold on, I...

1010
00:57:37,778 --> 00:57:39,405
Stop. Not another word.

1011
00:57:39,405 --> 00:57:41,515
I understand why you keep me at arm's length.

1012
00:57:41,515 --> 00:57:43,326
But...

1013
00:57:43,326 --> 00:57:46,245
What's a little rain between us?

1014
00:57:46,245 --> 00:57:48,539
Those were your own words.

1015
00:57:48,539 --> 00:57:51,375
You said no matter what,

1016
00:57:51,375 --> 00:57:54,119
you'd stand in the rain with me.

1017
00:57:56,380 --> 00:57:58,415
Nothing else matters to me.

1018
00:57:59,759 --> 00:58:01,761
Why don't we...

1019
00:58:01,761 --> 00:58:04,805
face it side by side for once.

1020
00:58:04,805 --> 00:58:07,924
With you, I feel like I can handle it.

1021
00:58:10,811 --> 00:58:12,643
Because

1022
00:58:13,272 --> 00:58:15,766
I like you.

1023
00:58:23,991 --> 00:58:27,652
But right now, I...

1024
00:58:45,263 --> 00:58:47,139
I told you

1025
00:58:47,139 --> 00:58:50,050
to keep quiet.

1026
00:59:16,210 --> 00:59:18,787
I can't get a single word in.

1027
00:59:20,047 --> 00:59:22,123
I'm not going anywhere.

1028
00:59:23,593 --> 00:59:26,419
How could I leave you behind?

1029
01:00:16,329 --> 01:00:18,412
You're really not going to the US?

1030
01:00:18,412 --> 01:00:21,579
Life without you and Woo Joo
is unthinkable now.

1031
01:00:24,537 --> 01:00:26,037
You like me?

1032
01:00:26,037 --> 01:00:27,348
It's Sun Tae Hyung, isn't it?

1033
01:00:27,348 --> 01:00:29,225
I thought you might waver.

1034
01:00:29,225 --> 01:00:31,245
This stays a secret at work.

1035
01:00:31,245 --> 01:00:34,954
Woo Hyun Jin is my girlfriend.

1036
01:00:34,954 --> 01:00:36,621
[Seoul Family Court]
What is this?

1037
01:00:36,621 --> 01:00:37,704
Hyun Jin.

1038
01:00:37,704 --> 01:00:40,370
Let's just get some good sleep.

1039
01:00:40,370 --> 01:00:42,028
Woo Joo disappeared.

1040
01:00:42,028 --> 01:00:42,829
Sun Woo Joo!

1041
01:00:42,829 --> 01:00:43,697
Woo Joo!

1042
01:00:43,697 --> 01:00:45,540
Woo Joo!
